('201412040914145', '201412021016554', 'qulaity enhanceent cell ', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">To:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mr. Preshan Daudzai<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AAJ Newspaper<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;\r\npadding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;border:none;\r\nmso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;padding:0in;mso-padding-alt:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Peshawar<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><b><u><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">REPORT ABOUT ONE DAY WORKSHOP ON <o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><b><u><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&ldquo;WHAT IS PLAGIARISM AND USE OF TURNITIN&rdquo;<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;</span></u></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The Quality Enhancement Cell, Islamia College Peshwar has organized one day seminar on &ldquo;<b>What is Plagiarism and Use of Turnitin</b>&rdquo; held on December 03 ,2014 for the PhD faculty members at the Video Conference Room, Islamia College Peshawar.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Mr. Ajmal Khan, Vice-Chancellor, ICP was the Chief Guest. Prof. Dr. Sareer Badshah, Registrar, ICP was also present at the occasion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Dr. Sajjad Ahmad Khan, Deputy Director-QEC was the Resource person. Most of the PhD faculty members were present in the workshop.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The workshop aim at apprising the PhD faculty members about Plagiarism and how to detect it through software called Turnitin. The participants were also educated about the use of the said software. They were informed about the HEC policy on plagiarism.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Imtiaz Hussain<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Analyst-QEC<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Islamia College Peshawar<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412080154134', '201412080135504', 'History of Islamia College Peshawar', '<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td width=\"83%\"> <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Islamia College Peshawar, the symbol of academic excellence is rich in history. Its building, which is the best embodiment of Muslim civilization in south Asia and its lush green lawns attract visitors from all over the country and abroad. It is not only the culminating point of the Aligarh Movement, it is in fact the beautiful combination of Aligarh and Deoband Schools of Thought. Being the breeding ground of the Pashtun intelligentsia, this great seat of learning is the place, where diamonds are skimmed since 1913. Moreover, Islamia College Peshawar was destined to become mother institution of the three universities and several colleges on its campus. The credit of this goes to Sir Sahibzada Abdul Qayyum, who is commonly called The Sir Sayyed of the Frontier and his sincere colleagues, who founded Islamia College Peshawar in 1913.</span></p></td>\r\n    <td width=\"17%\"><strong><img src=\"http://www.icp.edu.pk/images/stories/founder.jpg\" border=\"0\" title=\"Sir Sahibzada Abdul Qayyum Khan, The Founder\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" /></strong></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td colspan=\"2\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\"><img src=\"http://www.icp.edu.pk/images/stories/about-us.jpg\" border=\"0\" width=\"650\" height=\"150\" style=\"border-radius: 15px;\" alt=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Islamia College Peshawar is the best example of endowments. According to the Board of Trustees, the College, which is spread over 300 acres of land, has 1089 Jaribs cultivable land in Harichand, Rai Killi and Tarnab, (District Charsadda). In addition to this there are 395 shops and flats in the Khyber Bazaar Peshawar and main bazaar Charsadda.Â </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Quaid-e-Azam Muhammad Ali Jinnah visited this College in 1936, 1945 and 1948. Quaid-e-Azam who became lifelong honorary member of the Khyber Union ICP in 1936 made the College one of the heirs of his property in 1939. The Quaid Trust later on paid an amount of Rs.1, 08, 11, 600 /- in different installments to the College.</span></p> </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n   ', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412080200115', '201412080135504', 'Quaid-e-Azam Muhammad Ali Jinnah Will', '  <table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td width=\"83%\"> <p>Â </p>\r\n<p class=\"welcome\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: verdana,geneva; color: #000000;\">... All my residuary estate including the corpus that may fall after the lapse of life interest or otherwise to be divided into three parts - and I bequeath one part to Aligarh University - one part to Islamia College Peshawar and one part to Sindh Madrassa of Karachi ...</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"right\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: verdana,geneva; color: #000000;\"><em>Quaid-e-Azam s Will, Bombay, May 30, 1939</em></span></p> </td>\r\n    <td width=\"17%\"><span style=\"color: #333333; font-size: medium;\"><img src=\"http://www.icp.edu.pk/images/stories/quaid.jpg\" border=\"0\" title=\"Quaid-e-Azam Muhammad Ali Jinnah\" width=\"134\" height=\"176\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" /></span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n  ', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412080207235', '201412080136524', 'About Vice-Chancellor', '  <p align=\"justify\">Prof. Dr. Habib Ahmad (<em>TI</em>) took  charge as the Â Vice Chancellor, Islamia  College, Peshawar on July 29, 2016. Prof. Dr. Habib Ahmad (<em>TI</em>) also remain as the acting Vice Chancellor, Hazara  University from August 03, 2015 to July 28, 2016. Prof. Habib Ahmad is having a  vast experience of over 29 years in teaching, research and development and is  ranked among the most privileged scientists of the country. He has served both  nationally and internationally reputed organizations including WWF-Pakistan,  Higher Education Department Khyber Pakhtunkhwa and Pakistan Agricultural  Research Council before joining Hazara University as a professor in March 2005.Â </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n  He started his career as a scientific officer by  joining National Agricultural Research Center Islamabad on February 02, 1986.  Where he made valuable contributions toward the establishment of cytogenetics  laboratory that grew later into Cytogenetics Program of international repute.  As technical coordinator in WWF, he introduced the discipline of Ethnobotany at  the university level, which is growing at quantum rate and contributing a lot  to the conservation of natural resources of Pakistan.Â </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n  Since 2005, Dr. Habib Ahmad has been an integral  part of Hazara University and is playing a critical role in the developmental  matters of the University. As Dean Faculty of Science, he has provided a  platform for academic leadership and excellence in teaching and research.  Further, his immense role to strengthen Hazara University through capacity  building of the young faculty as well as students and to prepare them to  compete at the global level is inevitable. Establishment of new academic  departments like Botany, Genetics, Zoology, Bioinformatics, Center for Human  Genetics and giving them international recognition are the ultimate  contributions of Dr. Habib Ahmad, and his these services continues till this  day.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n  Over the recent years, he has published more than  200 research papers in peer reviewed international journals and 22 books  addressing our national concerns. It is worthwhile to mention that Dr. Habib  Ahmad has successfully supervised 9 PhDs and 98 MPhil scholars in the most  challenging areas of life sciences. He has developed a high yielding rapeseed  variety \"Hasnain-2013\" for enhancing edible oil production in Pakistan.  Government of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa has approved the variety for commercial  cultivation. In addition, Dr. Habib Ahmad also has the credit of successfully  introducing a new cropÂ <em>Pepino</em>Â in Pakistan.Â </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n  To date, he has completed 13 research projects,  worth millions of rupees and another seven research projects are ongoing under  his complete or partial supervision. Research output of Dr. Habib Ahmad can be  viewed on Google Scholar in the form of 248 articles, with 997 citations, 17  h-index and 33 i-10 index. He has represented Pakistan in 15 international  scientific forums and has the honour of being the first Muslim Scholar and  Pakistani, who remained as a member on the Board of Directors, Society for  Conservation Biology, USA.Â </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n  Services of Dr. Habib Ahmad have been widely  acknowledged by the civil society through conferring him the Best Researcher of  Award Hazara University 2006, Teacher of the Year 2007 by UNESCO/Ministry of  Education Government of Pakistan, National Talent Award 2008, Best Performance  Award-2011 and Productive Scientist Award for the year 2011, 2012, 2013 and  2014. In recognition of his contributionsÂ to theÂ field of  Cytogenetics, the Government of Pakistan awarded him the prestigious civil  awardÂ <em><strong>Tamgha-e-Imtiaz</strong></em>in March 2011.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n  Prof. Dr. Habib Ahmad has already made a huge  impact in transforming Hazara University as one of the best seat of learning  and place for genuine research within the country. Moreover, his current  position as a Vice Chancellor Islamia College, Peshawar is widely seen as a turning point in shaping the  future of Islamia College, Peshawar and our coming generations through high  quality education.</p>\r\n  ', 'General ', 2, 0, '2015-10-28'),
