"font-size: 8pt; font-family: verdana,geneva; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Total</span></strong></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td style=\"width: 184pt;\" width=\"245\">\r\n            <p style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 2.88pt 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: verdana,geneva; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Rs.39.786 Million</span></strong></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\">\r\n    <ul class=\"ul_star\">\r\n        <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Higher Education Commission has sanctioned Rs.1,70000 for construction of firing range in Swabi Campus for the shooting activities of Khyber Rifle Students Society in general and training of University Chowkidar in particular.</span></li>\r\n        <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Govt. of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa has donated 4000 kannals land free of charges for Swabi Campus and its Environment department has already sent the draft for signing MOU on Bio-diversity park. <br />\r\n        <br />\r\n        </span></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Establishment of ICP Campus at Malakpura District Abbottabad</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\">\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Secretary Higher Education Department Convene a meeting on 16.06.2011 and invited the Secretary to Govt. of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Auqaf, Hajj, Religious &amp; Minority Affairs Department, Administrator Auqaf and Vice Chancellor Islamia College, Peshawar for discussion on the subject matter.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Representative of Auqaf Department demanded Rs.3,97000/- per month has rent of the Banglow at Malakpura Abbottabad for Establishment of ICP Campus.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Vice Chancellor Islamia College, Peshawar offered maximum monthly rent @Rs.80000/- per month for the proposed building of the Auqaf Department Govt. of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. The Administrator Auqaf was not agreed with the monthly rent quoted by the Vice Chancellor and he was stressing for further negotiation.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The new Vice Chancellor is agreed to continue the negotiation with the Administrator Auqaf for the fixation of the rent of aforesaid building.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412230117086', '201412160324106', 'DSA Scholarships', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">532 students are awarded scholarships by the following (18) Governmental and Non-Governmental Organizations.</span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\">\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Punjab Endowment Educational Scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">HEC / USAID Financial Aid Program.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">DIYA Pakistan scholarships (NGO).</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Saifullah Trust scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">National Bank of Pakistan Financial Loan Program.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">HEC&rsquo;s need based merit scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">FATA Educational Foundation Scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Frontier Education scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">OWN A Student project scholarships (NGO).</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Board&rsquo;s scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Senior Alumni Association&rsquo;s scholarships ICP.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">FATA / FR&rsquo;s Scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Employees Education Foundation scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Baitul-Mal scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Fuji Foundation scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Charsadda Anjuman scholarships.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Mora scholarships of District Government.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Upper FATA Livelihood Development&nbsp; Program (LDP).</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412230119126', '201412160324106', 'DSA Societies Activities', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva; font-size: 12pt;\">Science and Technology Exhibition</span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Science &amp; Technology Society hold. Science &amp; Technology Exhibition on 6th &amp; 7th June, 2010 in which 80 institutions of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa participated. The names of the Institutions win prizes/certificates are given as below: </span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Abdul Wali Khan University Mardan </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Islamia College University Peshawar </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">F.G. Degree College Peshawar </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">ICMS Peshawar </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Green Montessori of School System Peshawar </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Qadims Luminer School Chinar Road University Town Peshawar </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Islamia Collegiate School Peshawar</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&emsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva; font-size: 12pt;\">Hiking Adventure Society</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The hiking / adventure society arranged its first visit to hilly areas in Galliat Hazara Division / Chitral during the year 2010 in which 40 students alongwith organizer and co-organizer participated. </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The group enjoyed the events of Shundur Mela w.e.f. 5th July to 11th July, 2010 and practically took part in the hiking under the supervision of organizer &amp; co-organizer. </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The members of Hiking &amp; Adventure Society displayed the banners of Islamia College Peshawar on hills and the organizer / co-organizer submitted the report of the said visit to me which is duly incorporated in the Annual Report of the University. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&emsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva; font-size: 12pt;\">Social Welfare and Awareness Society</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">250 members of Social Welfare &amp; Awareness Society initially arranged an orientation programmes in collaboration with the Regional office of Pakistan Red Crescent Society on 17th June 2010 in Khyber Union Hall and continued with the same programs in the last two years.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Society provided 230 volunteers to Pakistan Red Crescent Society. The events of the aforesaid programmes are properly preserved as record in the University. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&emsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva; font-size: 12pt;\">Khyber Literary and Debating Society</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">That after the inception of students societies in Islamia College, Peshawar, the Khyber Literary &amp; Debating Society arranged its 1st function in collaboration with the Ministry of Youth Affairs Islamabad on 23rd &amp; 24th July, 2010 at Gandhara University Peshawar.&nbsp; </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The students of all the Universities of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa participated in this regional level educational orientation programme. The students of Islamia College won the prizes in the major events as under:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_bullet_small\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Mr. Hammad Naushad, student of BS 4th Semester won Ist. prize in quiz competition, 2nd Prize in Essay writing and got the award for Pride of Performance in this event.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Mr. Ihtishamul Haq, student of 2nd year (Humanity group) won Ist. Prize in debating competition.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Mr. Kamal Alam and Waqas Ayub, 2nd year students remained runner up in Qirrat and singing competitions.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The activities of this society also continued in the last two years has been properly recorded is incorporate in the Annual report of the University.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&emsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva; font-size: 12pt;\">Khyber Islamic Cultural and Dramatic Society</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\">\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The cabinet of Khyber Islamic Cultural Society held its 1st meeting on 12th June, 2010 and planned a series of programs for the session 2010-2011 out of which the 1st program of Quirat competition for female students held in Khyber Union Hall held on 18.03.2011. They also undertaken a series of programs in the session 2010-2012. </span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Dramatic Society staged its 1st drama in Preston University Islamabad in December, 2011 and got 2nd position in the country. They also finalized the arrangement for staging the play Julius Caesar drama in Agha Khan Auditorium as per detail given below:</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Three days (21st,22nd and 24th of April 2012) for full dress rehearsals.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Four days (27th, 28th, 29th and 30th of April 2012) for final performances for students of Islamia College, guests from outside, Senior Alumini, Faculty members and families of actors and cabinets members of Dramatics Society.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">However the scheduled program was postponed by the then Vice Chancellor due to the opposition of some teachers who are against the mix gathering of Male &amp; Female students.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412230120576', '201412160324106', 'DSA Tasks Undertaken', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Tasks / Programs may be undertaken by the Directorate of Students Affairs in the Session 2012 - 2013</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_star\">\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Govt. of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa has recently introduced Naway Sahar Laptop Scheme for more than 500 eligible students have applied so for and its numbers are increasing day by day, the proforma sent by HED will be completed in September, 2012&nbsp; shall be approved by the Vice Chancellor before its submission to the quarter concerned.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Vice Chancellor as well as the members of Peripheral Campuses Committee will meet to decide the date of admission in Parachinar &amp; Sadda Campuses of Islamia College, Peshawar.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Vice Chancellor as well as members of Peripheral Campuses Committee will visit Swabi Campus so as to select the site for construction of firing range for which the funds are already sanctioned by the HEC.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Vice Chancellor will be requested to fix the date for signing MOU with the environment department of Govt. Khyber Pakhtunkhwa so that the Bio-diversity park may be established on the Swabi Campus.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The DIYA foundation Rawalpindi has requested for holding the scholarship distribution ceremony among 270 students after 5th September, 2012 in which in addition to the office bearers of NGO, Senior Alumini and Vice Chancellor will participate.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">The Vice Chancellor may be requested to fix the date for the meeting of indigenous scholarship committee for award of scholarship to 07 leftover M.Phil leading to Ph.D scholars.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28'),
('201412230140286', '201412230137204', 'Arabic Courses', '<p><strong>Courses  offered:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  B.S, M.A, M.Phil leading to Ph.D &amp; Ph.D<br>\r\n  <br>\r\n  <strong>Course Description:</strong> Arabic grammar( Morphology &amp;  Syntax) , Rhetoric, Criticism, Lexicology,Phonology &amp; Intonation, History  of Arabic Literature,Linguistics, Philology,Science of  Accents&amp;Dialects,Classical/Modern/Comparative &amp;Islamic  Literature,Research Methodology&amp; Art of Translation etc.<br>\r\n  <br>\r\n  <strong>Course Duration:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; B.S (8 semesters), M.A  (2 years), M.S/M.Phil&nbsp; (2 years), Ph.D&nbsp; (3 years)<br>\r\n  <br>\r\n  <strong>Course Eligibility:</strong> For B.S (F.A or equivalent),&nbsp;  For M.A (B.A or equivalent) , For M.S/M.Phil (M.A or equivalent) , For Ph.D  (M.S/M.Phil).</p>\r\n', 'General ', 55, 0, '2015-10-28');
