('201412230232026', '201412230219265', 'Scheme of Study (MSc)', '  <div>\r\n  <div>\r\n    <p>The Master Degree in Statistics is designed as a terminal degree, typically taken by students with backgrounds in one of the Natural, Physical, or Social Sciences. Graduates with a Master Degree are trained as data analysts capable of work in a variety of positions in government and industry.</p>\r\n    <p><strong>Scheme of studies:</strong></p>\r\n    <p>M.Sc. Statistics is a two years course with four semesters. Each semester have five courses, the details of these courses are as under:</p>\r\n    <table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\">\r\n      <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"118\"><p><strong>Semester</strong></p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"135\"><p><strong>Number of courses</strong></p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p><strong>Number of Major courses*</strong></p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p><strong>Number of Elective** courses</strong></p></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"118\"><p>1st semester</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"135\"><p>5</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p>5</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p>-</p></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"118\"><p>2nd semester</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"135\"><p>5</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p>4</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p>1</p></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"118\"><p>3rd semester</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"135\"><p>5</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p>5</p></td>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\" width=\"182\"><p>-</p></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td valign=\"top\